\begin_layout Standard
Cancer is arguably the most important disease in the modern world.
 According to the World Health Organization (WHO), there were 4.1 million
 new cancer cases, 8.2 million cancer deaths and 32.6 million people living
 with cancer (within 5 years of diagnosis) in 2012 worldwide 
